      "message": "[Critical] Line 255: 🔴 Critical Issues - The previous protection against calling `ensureDaemonStarted()` from the daemon executor was removed, but the method still schedules bootstrap work on `mExecutor` and then waits for it. If any daemon-executor callback calls this method while the daemon is not started, it self-deadlocks until timeout or indefinitely because of the wait bug above. Restore an explicit executor-thread guard using a reliable marker rather than relying on callers.\n```suggestion\ncheck(!onDaemonExecutor.get()) {\n    \"ensureDaemonStarted must not be called from the DaemonExecutor thread\"\n}\n```",
