      "message": "[Critical] Line 266: 🔴 Critical Issues - The timeout wait can become an indefinite wait when `remaining / 1_000_000` rounds down to `0`, so `ensureDaemonStarted()` may block forever instead of returning `false` after 25s. This can strand push handling and keep lifecycle resources inconsistent. Use the `(millis, nanos)` overload or clamp the millisecond value to at least 1.\n```suggestion\nval remainingMs \u003d TimeUnit.NANOSECONDS.toMillis(remaining)\nval remainingNs \u003d (remaining - TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toNanos(remainingMs)).toInt()\n@Suppress(\"PLATFORM_CLASS_MAPPED_TO_KOTLIN\")\n(bootstrapLock as java.lang.Object).wait(remainingMs, remainingNs)\n```",
      "revId": "93fce1658d404ad613276e47385e978554ff804a",
